After being on the run and living in tents for many years, David finally gets the palace. He finally has his place. Yet he feels a little guilty knowing the ark of the covenant is still living in a tent. He promises to build a temple but God says not to worry about it---He's fine with the tent living for a while longer. He then goes on to tell David that ---actually!--- a house will be established for him and his name will be considered one of the greatest of men. He promises David a lot of great things in chapter 17 verses 4-14 if you wanna check those out. David is obviously really grateful and prays with thanksgiving to God. “You, my God, have revealed to your servant that you will build a house for him. So your servant has found courage to pray to you.” (1 Chronicles‬ ‭17:25) >>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
God made the promise and THEN David had the courage to pray. What! Anyone else feel like they can't pray to God about certain things? Maybe you feel like you can't pray certain prayers? Might be time for a refresher. What are some of the promises God has made to you? His Word is full of them. Go there first; remind yourself of His promises; courage will be found; then start praying!

Good morning friends. Have a blessed day!

This is where I live, 
Isn't that wild? 
These past few months have been very different for me, with moving homes to new responsibilities and restrictions. I haven't been able to experience the simple pleasures of being in California. 
And when you haven't been to your favorite sunset beach in two/three months; 
you hysterically crack yourself up and lose it because you are so enthralled with the majesty and wonder that the creator bestows over. 
Freedom has gained a lot of weight and time has become so precious in this season and I am overwhelmed by the kindness and the grace that I received through Abba to take it one day at a time. 
Thankful for this moment to kick back and realize that each season brings various fruits: joy and mourning, pain and strength, laughter and tears, truth and lies, life and death, pruning and growth, freedom and captivity. 
It's a choice, it's sovereignty, it's free will. 
It's part of the journey in this vast universe and it draws you closer to the heartbeat of the one who longs for you and adores you: Yeshua. 
Embrace and surrender, 
Arise and soar into his arms that are wide open in every moment of your season. 
He has always been there, he will always be!
